#! <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
#! <TRANSFORMER
# TRANSFORMER_BEGIN EMPTY_FORMAT_MAPPER_NG,1,"""FGP Tools""",9430d0fe-e21e-426b-987d-f4de4b0c04ab,"Linked by Default",No,NO_PARALLELISM,,No,25241,YES,No,313,No,
# <p><strong>Description: </strong></p>
# <p>Custom transformer used to fill the resources{}.format when the format is missing or empty. The custom is using the corresponding resources{}.url to extract the format. </p>
# <p>In a first step, the custom transformer will analyse the URL:</p>
# <ul>
# <li>if the url contains the substring "service=wms" the format is WMS</li>
# <li>if the url contains the substring "mapserver" or "featureserver" the format is ESRI REST</li>
# <li>if the url ends with a file format extension (ex.: .shp) it takes the extension as the file format; except if the extension is .zip where it tries to find the original file format before being zipped (like CSV for the following url: blablabla.csv.zip)</li>
# </ul>
# <p>In a second step, the custom transformer will validate that the format extracted with the preceding rules is a valid format by checking if the format is present in the table Format.csv.</p>
# <p>In a third step, if the format is still unknown (format="other"), the custom transformer extract the MIME-content of header of the URL.  The MIME-content is than used to extract the format from the CSV file Mime_type.csv</p>
# <p><strong>Parameters</strong></p>
# <ul>
# <li>CSV_FORMAT: Name of the CSV table containing the list of valid fromat for the resources.</li>
# <li>CSV_MIME_TYPE: Name of the CSV table containing the MIME-type and the corresponding format.</li>
# <li>IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Name of the directoty containing the lookup tables.</li>
# <li>P-T_ABBR: Two letter abbreviation of the province (ex: ON for Ontario)</li>
# <li>URL_VALIDATION: Flag used to extract the header of the URL, can take two values: Yes: Extract the header in order to get the MIME-type; No: Do not extract the header.</li>
# </ul>
# <p><strong>Input Ports</strong></p>
# <ul>
# <li>DATA_INPUT: The input features to process</li>
# </ul>
# <p><strong>OUTPUT Ports</strong></p>
# <ul>
# <li>DATA_OUTPUT: The processed output features</li>
# <li>UNKNOWN_MIME_TYPE: The features with a MIME-TYPE not present in the MIME-type CSV file.</li>
# </ul>
# TRANSFORMER_END
#!   A0_PREVIEW_IMAGE="data:image/png;base64,"
#!   ARCGIS_COMPATIBILITY="ARCGIS_AUTO"
#!   ATTR_TYPE_ENCODING="SDF"
#!   BLOCKED_LOOPING="No"
#!   CATEGORY="&quot;FGP Tools&quot;"
#!   DESCRIPTION="&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;Custom transformer used to fill the resources{}.format when the format is missing or empty. The custom is using the corresponding resources{}.url to extract the format. &lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;In a first step, the custom transformer will analyse the URL:&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;if the url contains the substring &quot;service=wms&quot; the format is WMS&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;if the url contains the substring &quot;mapserver&quot; or &quot;featureserver&quot; the format is ESRI REST&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;if the url ends with a file format extension (ex.: .shp) it takes the extension as the file format; except if the extension is .zip where it tries to find the original file format before being zipped (like CSV for the following url: blablabla.csv.zip)&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;In a second step, the custom transformer will validate that the format extracted with the preceding rules is a valid format by checking if the format is present in the table Format.csv.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;In a third step, if the format is still unknown (format=&quot;other&quot;), the custom transformer extract the MIME-content of header of the URL.  The MIME-content is than used to extract the format from the CSV file Mime_type.csv&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;CSV_FORMAT: Name of the CSV table containing the list of valid fromat for the resources.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;CSV_MIME_TYPE: Name of the CSV table containing the MIME-type and the corresponding format.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Name of the directoty containing the lookup tables.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;P-T_ABBR: Two letter abbreviation of the province (ex: ON for Ontario)&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;URL_VALIDATION: Flag used to extract the header of the URL, can take two values: Yes: Extract the header in order to get the MIME-type; No: Do not extract the header.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;DATA_INPUT: The input features to process&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OUTPUT Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;DATA_OUTPUT: The processed output features&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;UNKNOWN_MIME_TYPE: The features with a MIME-TYPE not present in the MIME-type CSV file.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;"
